description:
&lt;p&gt;The Princess Alexandra Hospital – Harlow Site&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;We are seeking a dynamic Registered Pharmacy Technician to be part of our Pharmacy team based within the Princess Alexandra Hospital in Harlow, Essex.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In this role you will be responsible for providing an accurate and efficient service in the pharmacy dispensary and on wards, including supporting the new assessment unit. We would expect applicants to be highly motivated and responsible individuals with a passion for customer service and team work available full time 37.5 hours a week to cover a 7 day service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we can offer support to develop your career within a friendly and supportive team of professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For this role you will need to be a Pharmacy Technician registered with the GPhC with experience of medicines reconciliation at ward level. You will also be required to have achieved a Regional Checking Accreditation or a Medicines Management qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHannah LeMarEmail addressh.lemar@nhs.netTelephone number01279 827056Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Available for calls or informal visits between the hours of 9am and 4pm&lt;/p&gt;
